<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>Welcome to Tanuki</title>
    <style type="text/css" media="screen">
    body {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', Helvetica, sans-serif;
        font-size: 11pt;
        background-color: #f5f4ef;
        color: #000305;
    }

    #header {
        margin: 0 auto;
        width: 540px;
    }

    div.top {
        background-color: #fff;
        margin: 0 auto 20px auto;
        padding: 15px 20px 0 20px;
        width: 540px;
        border-radius: 10px;
        -moz-border-radius: 10px;
        -webkit-border-radius: 10px;
    }

    h1 {
        margin: 20px 0;
        padding: 0;
        font-size: 22pt;
    }

    h1 em {
        display: block;
        font-style: normal;
        font-size: 12pt;
        color: #777a7c;
    }

    h2 {
        margin: 0 0 15px 0;
        padding: 0;
        font-size: 16pt;
    }

    #next ol {
        margin: 0;
        padding-bottom: 25px;
    }

    #next li {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        font-size: 16pt;
        font-weight: bold;
        color: #c74451;
    }

    #next li span {
        font-size: 11pt;
        font-weight: normal;
        color: #000305;
    }

    code {
        font-family: 'DejaVu Sans Mono', 'Bitstream Vera Sans Mono', Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, 'Courier New', monospace;
        font-size: 10pt;
        background-color: #fffccc;
        padding: 1px 3px;
    }

    #env div {
        padding-bottom: 25px;
    }

    #env table {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        border-collapse: collapse;
        color: #444;
    }

    #env table th {
        text-align: left;
    }

    #env table td {
        padding-left: 20px;
        font-size: 10pt;
    }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div id="header">
        <h1>It Works! <em>You have been granted one Tanuki.</em></h1>
    </div>
    <div class="top" id="next">
        <h2>What to do next</h2>
        <div>
            <p>Here's a few suggestions to get things going:</p>
            <ol>
                <li><span>To use a database, describe its contents in <code>schema/user</code>.</span></li>
                <li><span>To generate models from your schema, run <code>tanuki generate</code>.</span></li>
                <li><span>To add or edit controllers, navigate to <code>app/user</code>.</span></li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="top" id="env">
        <h2>Your setup</h2>
        <div><table>
            <tr><th>Ruby</th><td><%= RUBY_VERSION %> (<%= RUBY_RELEASE_DATE %>) [<%= RUBY_PLATFORM %>]</td></tr>
            <tr><th>Rack</th><td><%= Rack.version %> (on <%= ctx.env['SERVER_SOFTWARE'] %>)</td></tr>
            <tr><th>Tanuki</th><td><%= Tanuki::VERSION %></td></tr>
        </table></div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
